hail stanford hail stanford home of champions stanford home of champions celebrating stanford's scholar athlete heritage home championship history voices of champions campus perspectives becoming a champion hail stanford hail by brad lawson 12 science technology & society stanford men's volleyball tweet a stanford scholar athlete is more than just an athlete but even beyond being balanced both academically and athletically a stanford scholar athlete has interests and dreams that extend beyond the court or classroom for me one of these passions is music although people are often a little surprised at first when i take the floor at maples pavilion and belt out the national anthem my love for music started at a young age when i joined my school choir in fourth grade since then i ve been involved in a musical joined two bands and even tried to produce a few recordings it's amazing how the stanford community has supported me and given me opportunities to become not only a better scholar athlete but also a more well rounded person i hope you enjoy this version of hail stanford hail brad lawson is a junior outside hitter on the stanford men's volleyball team which won the 2010 ncaa championship he was named 2010 mpsf player of the year and was co mvp of the ncaa championship a 2010 first team all american brad comes from iolani school in honolulu hawaii search for voices of champions featured interview with a fan by chase beeler 11 football soccer team 3 the other kind of championship by bobby warshaw 11 stanford men's soccer allyse 5 allyse ishino the sunrise after a stormy night by jenny peter 12 women's gymnastics tori 2 crop1 almost there by tori pennings 12 stanford cross country and track christen featured riptide by christen press 11 stanford women's soccer baldwin why vs how by doug baldwin 11 stanford football voices villa brenda villa balance and belief by kim krueger 11 stanford women's water polo stanford athletes holding ncaa championship plaque my extra step 